{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dd318ab3-4243-40d5-97ca-8ddaed11c0ba","content":"Here's how to migrate your xUnit.net test project to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n**1. Update packages** in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n<!-- Add -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.0.0\" />\n```\n\nKeep your existing `xunit` 2.9.3 package reference.\n\n**2. Enable MTP** in your `.csproj` (or `Directory.Build.props`):\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**3. Run tests** the same way:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test\n```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `xunit.runner.mtp` v1.0.0+ is the MTP runner for xUnit.net, replacing `xunit.runner.visualstudio`.\n- The `TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport` property ensures `dotnet test` uses MTP instead of VSTest.\n- Your test code itself doesn't need any changes.\n- If you use `runsettings` files, note that MTP uses a different configuration model — check the [Microsoft.Testing.Platform docs](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/testing/microsoft-testing-platform) for equivalents.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"efb4870d-9a46-42dc-a7d2-72b9f73c6795","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":409,"requestId":"6806:24EAAB:2960B08:2DAA074:69FD341C"},"id":"fd2bf6a3-fd71-4e04-a88a-b60b11241897","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:53:56.604Z","parentId":"54ab743a-7eeb-4985-9634-0736862ad6e5"}
